items.title: As the Shutdown Pain Grows, Trump Attends to Other Matters
items.description: The president attended a Halloween party Friday and called attention to the marble renovation of a White House bathroom.

items.title: How Britain Got Investors to Line Up for Nuclear Power
items.description: Developers have finally broken ground on the project, known as Sizewell C, but getting there meant navigating wary investors and local opposition.

items.title: Trump’s Latest White House Makeover: The Lincoln Bathroom in Marble and Gold
items.description: President Trump said the new look was “totally in keeping” with the era of Abraham Lincoln.

items.title: It’s Halloween Night, and New York Is Decked Out in All Its Gory Glory
items.description: The spooky season comes to end with what is billed as the world’s largest Halloween parade.

items.title: Twenty Years Later, Atrocities Haunt Darfur Again
items.description: The world seems unable, or unwilling, to do much to stop a new struggle on an old battlefield, as atrocities sweep villages and towns.
